The paper deals with the manipulation of stable matchings, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also provides algorithms for calculating the desired strategies, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the limitations imposed by given preferences, which is related to social choice theory (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
